  "prompt": "Can Google help me track my lost Android phone by the IMEI number?",
  "response": "Google itself does not provide a service to track lost Android phones using the IMEI number. However, you can track a lost Android phone using Google's Find My Device service, which requires that your device is connected to your Google account and has location services enabled.\n\nHere are the steps to track your lost Android phone:\n\n1. **Go to Find My Device**: Visit the Google Find My Device website (https://www.google.com/android/find) or use the Find My Device app on another Android device.\n\n2. **Sign in**: Log in with the Google account associated with your lost device.\n\n3. **Locate your device**: If your phone is turned on and connected to the internet, you should see its location on the map.\n\n4. **Options**: From there, you can ring the device, lock it, or erase its data.\n\nIf you have lost your phone and do not have access to Google services, your best option is to contact your carrier. They may be able to assist you in tracking the phone using its IMEI number or help you block the device to prevent unauthorized use. Additionally, you can report the loss to local authorities, as they may assist in recovery if the phone is found.",
